headlines.description: — Orlando’s Moritz Wagner appeared to briefly get knocked out by a punch to the back of the head after starting a fight in the first half...
headlines.shortLinkText: Three players ejected as Pistons-Magic scuffle in first half

headlines.description: — Rui Hachimura matched his career high with 30 points and converted a pivotal three-point play to help the Washington Wizards pull away for a 127-102 victory over the Phoenix Suns on Wednesday night in a meeting of depleted teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rui Hachimura helps Wizards beat short-handed Suns, 127-102

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving scored 15 of his 28 points in the fourth quarter, Kevin Durant had 26 points and a season-high 16 rebounds and the Brooklyn Nets won their 10th straight game, 108-107 over the short-handed Atlanta Hawks on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets win 10th straight, beating short-handed Hawks 108-107

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — The math wasn't hard. The Miami Heat got a lot of points off turnovers, and nearly went the whole game without giving up any.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat get past Lakers 112-98, climb over .500 at 18-17

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan compared the Chicago Bulls' success this season against the Eastern Conference's best teams to being chased by a dog.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan scores 42 points, Bulls beat Bucks 119-113 in OT

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson ducked and smiled as celebrating New Orleans Pelicans teammates poured bottles of water over him. Moments later, Trey Muprhy III pretended to place a crown on Williamson's head — a fitting gesture after a memorable game which, by the...
headlines.shortLinkText: Williamson scores career-high 43, Pelicans top Timberwolves

events.name: Utah Jazz at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Just weeks ago, the Golden State Warriors might not have pulled off a win like this without their superstars on the court.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jordan Poole has 26 points, Warriors rally past Jazz

headlines.description: — Malik Monk scored 33 points, including the tiebreaking free throw with 0.7 seconds left, and the Sacramento Kings came back from down 19 points late in the third quarter to beat the Denver Nuggets 127-126 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Monk scores 33, hits winning free throw as Kings top Nuggets
